ge diskutiert, wie weitreichend die ökologischen Konsequenzen unseres steigenden Verbrauchs an Batterien sein werden.  afunded by Leuphana Universität Lüneburg  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 4aAkku. 4aBatterien. 4aElektrizität. 4aElektromobilität. 4aInternet. 4aKultur. 4aMedien. 4aMediensoziologie. 4aMedienwissenschaft. 4aNachhaltigkeit. 4aTechnik. 4aTechniksoziologie. 4aÖkologie. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh  aBatteries.  aCulture.  aEcology.  aElectricity.  aElectromobility.  aInternet.  aMedia Studies.  aMedia.  aRechargeable Battery.  aSociology of Media.  aSociology of Technology.  aSustainability.  aTechnology.1 aDittmann, Frank, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGaderer, Rupert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHagen, Wolfgang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHauss, Philipp, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHille, Laura, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHintz, Eric S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKeller, Jonas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKröger, Fabian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMiggelbrink, Monique, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMüggenburg, Jan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMüggenburg, Jan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRieger, Stefan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/v